This is the Homeric sequel: the tale of Ulysses, beset by a series of
ever-more fantastic adventures on the way home from the Trojan War to
his wife, patient Penelope. The vivid adventures of our ill-fated
protagonist come to life in Butler's prose translation, told in a highly
readable modern voice, informed by archaic consciousness.--J.B. Hare

